2 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Study on consolidation of legal services. (1) For the interim following
3 the 69th legislative session, the general government interim budget committee shall study issues related to the
4 consolidation of legal services across state agencies and discrepancies in the compensation for legal
5 occupations across state agencies.
6 (2) By September 15, 2025, the department of administration shall report to the general
7 government interim budget committee on the following:
8 (a) the distribution of hourly wage rates of lawyers and other legal occupations in state agencies;
9 (b) a comparison of state pay rates and benefits to rates and benefits paid to lawyers and other
10 legal occupations in the private sector;
11 (c) considerations or explanations for differences in the pay rates across state agencies;
12 (d) an explanation on how pay rates for lawyers and other legal occupations are set across state
13 agencies; and
14 (e) the extent to which pay exceptions are made and for what purposes.
15 (3) By June 30, 2026, the department of administration shall provide to the general government
16 interim budget committee a proposal to consolidate legal services across state agencies, including a proposed
17 organizational structure and an estimate of the costs and benefits of consolidation. The proposal must also
18 include a proposed fee structure that would cover the costs of the consolidated legal services unit.
19 (4)(3) The general government interim budget committee shall complete the study by September 15,
20 2026, and report its findings and recommendations, including potential legislation, to the 70th legislature and to
21 the judicial branch, law enforcement, and justice interim budget committee.
22 (5)(4) The general government interim budget committee shall invite the members of the state
23 administration and veterans' affairs interim committee, the general government budget committee, and the
24 judicial branch, law enforcement, and justice interim budget committee to each of its meetings to participate in
25 the study.
